HEADWORD: Hecatompedon
<hw>Hec`a*tom"pe*don</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/
hundred feet long, <?/ <?/ the Parthenon; <?/ hundred + <?/ foot.]</ety>
<fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>A name given to the old Parthenon at Athens,
because measuring 100 Greek feet, probably in the width across the
stylobate.</def>⟦br⟧
